    • Method Detail

      • isVirtual

        public boolean isVirtual()
        Specified by:
        isVirtual in interface BeanAccess
        Overrides:
        isVirtual in class BeanAccessPrototype<BEAN extends Bean>
        Returns:
        true if this BeanAccess belongs to a virtual Bean. Virtual means that the prototype of the bean has been created via BeanPrototypeBuilder.createPrototype(Class, String, Bean...) and represents a class (interface) that does not exist as Java Class, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        BeanPrototypeBuilder.createPrototype(Class, String, Bean...)
